      <hedline>
        <hl1>Which Way For Amtrak?</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You describe David Gunn, who was ousted as Amtrak's president, as ''holding down costs without dismantling the railroad.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You describe David Gunn, who was ousted as Amtrak's president, as ''holding down costs without dismantling the railroad.''</p>
        <p>As a daily Amtrak commuter who will soon be paying more than $1,000 for his monthly ticket, I must ask: Whose costs was Mr. Gunn was holding down?</p>
        <p>Michael Idinopulos  Philadelphia, Nov. 10, 2005</p>
      </block>
